cs.CL, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.SD, cs.LG 

This paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to map between laymen's terms and medical concepts in social media messages. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with NLP and related topics. The paper also involves information retrieval (IR) techniques to extract relevant phrases from social media messages, making cs.IR (Information Retrieval) another likely category. The paper also involves machine learning techniques such as word vector representations, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) a possible category. Additionally, the paper deals with healthcare-related topics, making cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) possible categories as well.
